==English==
===Noun phrase===
'''field goal''' (''pl.'' '''field goals''')
#{{fb}} When the ball is kicked through the uprights and over the crossbar (not after a [[touchdown]]) for 3 points
#: ''He kicked a 33 yard '''field goal''' just before the half''
#{{basketball}} A made shot that was not a [[free throw]]
#: ''He got six '''field goals''' in the first half, two from three point land.''